        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 26 at 8:23PM CDT until June 26 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 823 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near South Haven, or
near Hobart, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Chesterton, Boone Grove, Portage, South Haven, Valparaiso, Town of
Pines, Beverly Shores, Burns Harbor, Ogden Dunes, Porter, Dune Acres,
Wheeler, Lakes of the Four Seasons, and Hebron.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
